# Copy this file to .env (or .env.local) and fill in the values.
# Vite only exposes variables prefixed with VITE_ to the browser.

# ── Route planner — HERE (map + routing + search) ─────────────────────────
# The Check-route planner uses HERE directly:
#   • HERE Maps API for JavaScript — the `vector.normal.logistics` basemap with
#     the HGV/truck "vehicle restrictions" overlay (mode "active & inactive").
#     Entered truck size/weight is applied via the layer's setVehicleSpecs() so
#     the overlay highlights limits that apply to the current vehicle.
#   • HERE Routing API v8 — transportMode=truck routes with the entered
#     vehicle[height|width|length|grossWeight|weightPerAxle] restrictions.
#   • HERE Geocoding & Search v7 — geocode / discover / autosuggest / lookup for
#     the From/To/stop fields.
# All three share ONE read-scoped key. It is read from the env (never hardcoded);
# when unset, the planner shows a themed "not configured" state.
#
# ADR / hazardous goods: HERE expects specific hazardous *types* rather than a
# boolean, so the ADR checkbox is intentionally NOT translated into an arbitrary
# type for either the overlay or routing. This is a deferred typed-selector item.
#
#   VITE_HERE_API_KEY   a HERE REST + JS API key from the HERE platform.
VITE_HERE_API_KEY=

# ── Vehicle-location modal map — Amazon Location Service (optional) ────────
# Amazon Location is NO LONGER used by the Check-route planner (that is HERE now,
# see above). These values power ONLY the vehicle-location modal's MapLibre map,
# which drops a marker at the vehicle's last reported position. No routing or
# geocoding happens here.
#
# Only the key + region are required; if either is missing the modal's map shows
# a themed "not configured" state and the rest of the app is unaffected.
#
#   VITE_AWS_LOCATION_API_KEY   the Amazon Location API key VALUE (looks like
#                               "v1.public.xxxxx") — NOT the key ARN. A READ-ONLY
#                               maps key. The modal renders the "Standard" road
#                               basemap, which is a LEGACY v0 HERE "Explore Truck"
#                               Map resource, so the key's policy needs the legacy
#                               map actions on that map's ARN:
#                                 geo:GetMapStyleDescriptor, geo:GetMapTile,
#                                 geo:GetMapGlyphs, geo:GetMapSprites
#                                 on  arn:aws:geo:<region>:<acct>:map/TruckMapDispoChat
#                               (plus geo-maps:GetTile only if the modal ever
#                               shows the v2 Satellite/Hybrid imagery). It needs NO
#                               geo-places / geo-routes grants — there is no
#                               geocoding or routing in the modal.
#   VITE_AWS_LOCATION_REGION    the key's region, e.g. eu-central-1
#
# The map resource must live in VITE_AWS_LOCATION_REGION (eu-central-1).
VITE_AWS_LOCATION_API_KEY=
VITE_AWS_LOCATION_REGION=eu-central-1
# Legacy HERE Explore Truck map resource name used for the modal's road basemap.
# Optional — defaults to "TruckMapDispoChat" when unset.
VITE_AWS_LOCATION_TRUCK_MAP_NAME=TruckMapDispoChat
